				<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">OTR</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Telecomix Crypto Munitions Bureau</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<a name="What_is_OTR_encryption.3F" id="What_is_OTR_encryption.3F"></a><h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=OTR&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1" title="Edit section: What is OTR encryption?">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">What is OTR encryption?</span></h3>
<p>Off-the-Record Messaging, commonly referred to as OTR, is a cryptographic protocol that provides strong encryption for instant messaging conversations. OTR uses a combination of the AES symmetric-key algorithm, the Diffieâ€“Hellman key exchange, and the SHA-1 hash function. In addition to authentication and encryption, OTR provides forward secrecy and malleable encryption.
</p><p><b>Limitations:</b>Due to limitations of the protocol, OTR does not support multi-user group chat as of 2009 or encrypted file transfers, but these may be implemented in the future. Support for encrypted audio or video is not planned.
</p>
